200 g Tre Stelle Paneer Cheese
340 g Pizza Dough
113 g Baby Spinach
165 mL Coconut Milk
2 tbsp Indian Spice Blend
6 g Garlic
30 g Ginger
14 g Cilantro
28 g Cashews
56 g Red Onion
2 tbsp All-Purpose Flour
1 tbsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
¼ tsp Pepper*
½ cup Tikka Sauce

Before starting, remove pizza dough from fridge and rest in a warm spot for 20 min.Preheat the oven to 475˚F.Wash and dry all produce.

Sprinkle both sides of the dough with flour. Divide the dough into two equal pieces (dbl for 4 ppl) and stretch each piece into a rough oval shape on a baking sheet. (NOTE: Use 2 baking sheets for 4 ppl). Let the dough rest in a warm place for 8-10 min.

While dough rests, peel, then cut half the onion (whole for 4 ppl) into 1/4-inch pieces. Peel, then mince or grate garlic. Peel, then mince or grate ginger. Roughly chop cilantro. Cut Tre Stelle Paneer into 1/2-inch cubes. Roughly chop cashews.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl) then half the onions, garlic, ginger, Indian Spice Blend and 1 tbsp sugar (dbl for 4 ppl). Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1-2 min. When fragrant, stir in Tre Stelle Paneer, coconut milk and tikka sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until reduced slightly, 3-5 min. When reduced, remove pan from heat. Add spinach and stir to wilt, 1 min.

With floured hands, stretch dough again into two oval shapes (NOTE: The dough should now hold its shape.) Spoon Saag Paneer onto dough. Sprinkle remaining onions over top. Bake pizzas in the middle of the oven, until golden brown and crisp, 14-18 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, bake pizzas in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through cooking.) Sprinkle chopped cilantro and cashews over pizzas.

Cut pizzas into slices and divide between plates.